    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Description\n\nConfigs for pyright/basedpyright have a user command for setting python path. But during migration to new standalone configs in 'lsp' dir a bug was introduced. `nvim_buf_create_user_command` calls a callback with a structured lua table, not a bare argument. In result this is what set for settings:\n\n```\n  - Settings: {\n      basedpyright = {\n        analysis = {\n          autoSearchPaths = true,\n          diagnosticMode = \"openFilesOnly\",\n          useLibraryCodeForTypes = true\n        }\n      },\n      python = {\n        pythonPath = {\n          args = \"/usr/bin/python3\",\n          bang = false,\n          count = -1,\n          fargs = { \"/usr/bin/python3\" },\n          line1 = 1,\n          line2 = 1,\n          mods = \"\",\n          name = \"LspPyrightSetPythonPath\",\n          nargs = \"1\",\n          range = 0,\n          reg = \"\",\n          smods = {\n            browse = false,\n            confirm = false,\n            emsg_silent = false,\n            hide = false,\n            horizontal = false,\n            keepalt = false,\n            keepjumps = false,\n            keepmarks = false,\n            keeppatterns = false,\n            lockmarks = false,\n            noautocmd = false,\n            noswapfile = false,\n            sandbox = false,\n            silent = false,\n            split = \"\",\n            tab = -1,\n            unsilent = false,\n            verbose = -1,\n            vertical = false\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n```\nNote `pythonPath` value.",
