            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> since you mentioned `nvim_buf_create_user_command` i wonder if [#3971](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/3971) is related\n\nIndeed, the `LspPyrightOrganizeImports` user command doesn't work also. But no, it's not related to this issue. I checked `client:exec_cmd` code, and it returns early if `executeCommandProvider.commands` server capability doesn't have requested command. And basedpyright (pyright also probably) doesn't advertise that it supports any commands:\n\n```lua\n    executeCommandProvider = {\n      commands = {},\n      workDoneProgress = true\n    }\n```\n\nYour suggestion to use `pcall` won't help, because `client:exec_cmd` doesn't error. It reports error via `vim.notify_once` and then returns. It never does any requests to the server.\n\nSo a possible fix could either be to remove `LspPyrightOrganizeImports` usercommand, because it uses a private command (not advertised via capabilities), or to use `client.request` as in PR to send request without additional checks. I used this command, and it worked before migration to `vim.lsp.config`.",
